Chapter:
Self-replicating groups

 Introductory text. To do.


Properties and Attributes



  true if G is self-replicating, and false otherwise.




 The argument of this property is aa regular rooted tree group G.









gap> subgroups:=AllSubgroups(AutT(2,2));
[ Group(()), Group([ (3,4) ]), Group([ (1,2) ]), Group([ (1,2)(3,4) ]), 
  Group([ (1,3)(2,4) ]), Group([ (1,4)(2,3) ]), Group([ (3,4), (1,2) ]), 
  Group([ (1,3)(2,4), (1,2)(3,4) ]), Group([ (1,3,2,4), (1,2)(3,4) ]), 
  Group([ (3,4), (1,2), (1,3)(2,4) ]) ]
gap> Apply(subgroups,G->RegularRootedTreeGroup(2,2,G));
gap> Apply(subgroups,G->IsSelfReplicating(G));
gap> subgroups;
[ false, false, false, false, false, false, false, true, true, true ]





  true if G has sufficient rigid automorphisms, and false otherwise.




 The argument of this property is a regular rooted tree group G









gap> subgroups:=AllSubgroups(AutT(2,2));
[ Group(()), Group([ (3,4) ]), Group([ (1,2) ]), Group([ (1,2)(3,4) ]), 
  Group([ (1,3)(2,4) ]), Group([ (1,4)(2,3) ]), Group([ (3,4), (1,2) ]), 
  Group([ (1,3)(2,4), (1,2)(3,4) ]), Group([ (1,3,2,4), (1,2)(3,4) ]), 
  Group([ (3,4), (1,2), (1,3)(2,4) ]) ]
gap> Apply(subgroups,G->RegularRootedTreeGroup(2,2,G));
gap> Apply(subgroups,G->HasSufficientRigidAutomorphisms(G));
gap> subgroups;
[ false, false, false, false, true, false, false, true, true, true ]





  The restriction of G to \mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n-1}).




 The argument of this attribute is a regular rooted tree group G \le\mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n}).









gap> G:=AutT(2,3);;
gap> ParentGroup(G);
Group([ (1,2), (1,3)(2,4), (3,4) ])
gap> last=AutT(2,2);
true





  The maximal extension of M(G)\le\mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n+1}) of G.




 The argument of this attribute is a self-replicating regular rooted tree group G \le\mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n}) with sufficient rigid automorphisms.







gap> G:=AutT(2,3);;
gap> MaximalExtension(G);
<permutation group with 11 generators>
gap> last=AutT(2,4);
true





  A self-replicating \mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n})-conjugate of G with sufficient rigid automorphisms. If G has sufficient rigid automorphisms then the output group has the same parent group (see ) as G.




 The argument of this attribute is a self-replicating regular rooted tree group G \le\mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n}).









gap> G:=SRGroup(2,3,6);;
gap> conjugates:=ShallowCopy(AsList(G^AutT(2,3)));
[ Group([ (1,5)(2,6)(3,7)(4,8), (1,3)(2,4)(5,7)(6,8), (1,2)(3,4) ]), 
  Group([ (1,5)(2,6)(3,8)(4,7), (1,3)(2,4)(5,8)(6,7), (1,2)(3,4) ]) ]
gap> Apply(conjugates,H->RegularRootedTreeGroup(2,3,H));
gap> for H in conjugates do Print(HasSufficientRigidAutomorphisms(H),"\n"); od;
true
false
gap> H:=conjugates[2];
Group([ (1,5)(2,6)(3,8)(4,7), (1,3)(2,4)(5,8)(6,7), (1,2)(3,4) ])
gap> IsSelfReplicating(H);
true
gap> RepresentativeWithSufficientRigidAutomorphisms(H);
Group([ (1,5)(2,6)(3,7)(4,8), (1,3)(2,4)(5,7)(6,8), (1,2)(3,4) ])
gap> last=conjugates[1];
true








Examples

 AutT. More to come. Grigorchuk, Hanoi, ...


  The regular rooted tree group \mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n}) as a permutation group of the k^{n} leaves of T_{k,n}.




 The arguments of this function are a degree k \in\mathbb{N}_{\ge 2} and a depth n \in\mathbb{N}.









gap> G:=AutT(2,2);
Group([ (1,2), (3,4), (1,3)(2,4) ])
gap> Size(G);
8





  A list containing conjugacy class representatives of all maximal self-replicating subgroups of G.



 The argument of this function is any regular rooted tree group, G









gap> ConjugacyClassRepsMaxSelfReplicatingSubgroups(AutT(2,2));
[ Group([ (1,3)(2,4), (1,2)(3,4) ]), Group([ (1,3,2,4), (1,2)(3,4) ]) ]





  A list of \mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n+1})-conjugacy class representatives of self-replicating subgroups of \mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n+1}) whose parent group is conjugate to G.



 The argument of this function is a regular rooted tree group G \le\mathrm{Aut}(T_{k,n}).









gap> A3:=RegularRootedTreeGroup(3,1,AlternatingGroup(3));;
gap> S3:=RegularRootedTreeGroup(3,1,SymmetricGroup(3));;
gap> A3_extn:=ConjugacyClassRepsSelfReplicatingSubgroupsWithConjugateProjection(A3);;
gap> S3_extn:=ConjugacyClassRepsSelfReplicatingSubgroupsWithConjugateProjection(S3);;
gap> Size(A3_extn);
5
gap> Size(S3_extn);
11
gap> NrSRGroups(3,2);
16
